title: Oklahoma State comes back in the 4th quarter, beats K-State 36-34
text:
Oklahoma State comes back in the 4th quarter, beats K-State 36-34 Published 6:50 PM CDT Oct 03, 2015 A Large Text Photos 
The Oklahoma State Cowboys didn't take a lead in the game until midway through the 4th quarter, and the late momentum, and a field goal with 37 seconds left, helped them beat the Kansas State Wildcats. 
The Cowboys won 36-34. Oklahoma State stopped K-State's final drive with an interception with 10 seconds left. 
With 6:06 left in the fourth quarter, the Cowboys scored a go-ahead touchdown to make the score 33-28. The Wildcats promptly marched down field and scored, taking the lead 34-33. The Cowboys had a successful 37-yard field goal that led to the win. 
K-State scored first in the game with a Kody Cook quarterback keeper with about 10 minutes left in the first quarter. The Cowboys tied it up less than three minutes later. The Wildcats didn't give up the lead, though, until the 4th quarter. 
At the half K-State was up 28-20.
